<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Adjusts the value of a branch target.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><Highlight kind="comment">/// All branch targets in AVR are rightshifted by 1 to take advantage</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of the fact that all instructions are aligned to addresses of size</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 2, so bit 0 of an address is always 0 This gives us another bit</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of precision.</Highlight></CodeLine>
